<br>
I use an all purpose hot key, being a druid and all.<br>
<br>
/target &lt;MA name here&gt;<br>
/sit off<br>
/assist %t<br>
<br>
this works great for a caster who meds, as Line 2 eliminates my need to get off my tushy. line 1 can be changed to who ever the MA is, or left blank. if there is a name there, then the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> %t </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->on line 3 does nothing, but if i leave it blank, then <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  %t </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->lets me assist who ever i already had targeted. I can use this button for just about anything with out modifying it each time i log in.<br>
<br>
